inn1.comm: a good start from Odoyo, angling that over the wicket across the lefthander who shoulders arms early
defended this time
on the money, the batsman comes forward to press that into short midwicket - Samad would have gone with a direct hit, but the throw was over the stumps
stays over the wicket to the righthander, sensibly enough, and finds a hint of swing away from him
strays down leg and that's glanced very fine for a straightforward four
steps forward, a hint of away swing, and that's defended easily enough into the covers
overstepping with the effort there, but there was a hint of movement away from the batsman
a wide this time, oops. A nervous start from Ongondo, and that wasn't even in the tramlines. Time to settle in, yet, though
better - straighter and the batsman can only shoulder arms as that flies through on a good length to the keeper
ooh! Great ball, half an appeal, but the bat just brushed the pad
defended forward this time
outside off and that flies through to the keeper
on the money, the batsman looks to play that into the on-side, dropping his hands down into the shot, but his top hand flies up off the bat with the impact
worked into the leg-side again for no run
plenty of swing in the air again for Odoyo, who leaves that one alone; good decision, not worth chasing that one
on the money - that's pressed into the leg-side
a half-shout for lbw but Parker's head is shaking pretty much as soon as the ball rapped the pad
places that on a good length and it's defended into the covers. Good bowling from Odoyo, giving nothing away so far this over
ooh! Late movement away there for Odoyo for one which was already quite wide, went wider, and had the batsman feeling for it. Nearly
a touch straighter results in a thickish outside edge, the batsman playing with the awayswing
defended forward, the ball not getting up very much on this pitch which is lacking pace
defended into the covers
more defence and the batsman rehearses his fresh-air shot
oh! Great ball, cutting back in off the seam and surprising the batsman as it raps into his pads
first aggressive stroke of the innings, the ball just straying onto the leg-side, and that's picked well off middle-and-leg, as it's clipped behind square

oh, great response, that's the ball, tempting the batsman - like an ice-cream seller when you're on a diet - to have a lick. He's tempted sure enough, but soon regrets his haste - still he misses and lives to fight another day
more defensiveness from the batsman
yet again more defence
and some more defence
the lefthander comes forward to try to work that into the leg-side, fails to get hold of it, and that's defended
bends over that one in leaning it into the leg-side
a maiden over from Odoyo - ending with a half-shout for lbw, that looked good on HawkEye, the ball pitching in line and straightening and hitting half-way up middle stump
steered down to third man
driven to a slightly wide mid-on
defended forward this time
expansive over-the-top cover-drive finally gets some impetus into his innings
pushed right up there and that's defended
right up there again and that's driven straight to mid-on
inside edge down to third man
driven down to mid-on, not quite off the middle
defended
hits a good channel again and Barnett finished outside off stump
back of a length, Samad come across and plays with the thick outside half of the bat out to point
round the wicket now ooh, that one seems to stop slightly in the pitch and Barnett nearly spoons it to the man at short, straight midwicket
this one holds its line from round the wicket and Barnett nearly pushes at it as it straightens
connects powerfully, frees his arms and launches over square cover for a welcome boundary
overstepping with the effort, there. Slightly fuller and closer to off stump, Barnett comes forward and plays back to the bowler
drives, but without any footwork and the ball flies off the inside half of the bat out to square leg
glanced away off the pads
defended back down the pitch
defended
more defence, coming forward to trap that one down into the ground
oh! Nearly very exciting... but wouldn't have mattered anyway as that's a big no-ball. Still, there was a very nice shape to that ball and that had the batsman chasing it
on the money, with a hint of swing, what else can you do with that ... except defend, as he does
width on that one, and that's hammered away through the covers with a flourish of a drive. Nice work
driven straight to cover
places that on a good length, it deviates cheekily, saying to the batsman, "Chase me"  - but, to his credit, he doesn't
ah! Play and a miss this time, over in the blink of an eye. Fishing outside off
hands fly up off the bat
driven to mid-on
souped over midwicket, picking up the length early, and with great hand/eye co-ordination he rocks on the front foot and plants that through the leg-side
edged away through third man, streakily enough
pushes that right up there, but checks the shot
defended forward and that's the first Powerplay over and done with
defended into the covers
defended forward
short, wide and that's gone! That's a disappointing end to Samad's innings, cutting straight to backward point for a catch that can only be described as regulation
defended forward
nicely timed back foot push through the covers to get off the mark but it's chased down by a pair of fielders just inside the boundary
strays on to leg and that's nudged into the midwicket region
defended first up
... and he nearly gets a wicket second ball - Barnett not knowing where that leading edge had gone - over the slips in fact
down the off-side - no doubt that was wide, there
not a great ball, and not great fielding - diving inside the long-on boundary from that on-drive. Canada's fifty comes up
right up there and defended
on the money and that's pushed off the backfoot into the covers
cut off the back foot straight to the man at backward point
hit aerially to fine leg and the batsman watched anxiously in case he was caught - but the ball fell safe
defended into the covers. A run, perhaps? "No!"
driven slowly to the off-side
worked into the covers this time
defended this time
oh, great ball - ah, a no-ball - still, that was a play and a miss, and that will encourage the bowler
a big stride forward to defend
punched down the ground - there's no need to run for that
eased down through third man, opening the blade, which resulted in a controlled outside edge
that won't win the "Pretty shot of the year" award, an ill-timed pull, however a four's a four - that's three in succession - and that races away behind square
oh, a touch of swing there
much better timing and another four - this time clipped away well off the toes and that races behind backward square; nothing wrong with that shot at all
scorching over closes with another boundary, this time a rocket of a straight drive through mid-off
played off the back foot through point
thinks about swivel-pulling that off the back foot, and plays the shot without much power

what a catch! What a catch. One of those you never want to be under - the ball was hit high - and higher - downwind from a mistimed pull. Mishra takes his time to have a quick glance to see where the rope is, takes a few steps back, and allows himself six or seven inches inside the rope, taking the ball at head height, palms upwards
a hint of swing away and that's left alone first up
short, a touch of width, and Billcliff's quickly on to that one, crashing it away off the back foot through point
shorter, still wide, and that's dinked behind point off the back foot
not the best start - drops that one short, wide, and on this slow surface the ball sits up and requests, nay begs, to be smacked through cover and Bagai duly obliges
better, much better, fuller and that's defended quietly
loop this time, and full; that's well bowled again
defended off the back foot into the covers
more defence
on the money, defended
oooh, that nips off the seam away from the batsman who nibbles at it, but his bat bites fresh air
defended this time
left alone
left alone again
defended this time
oh, that one didn't carry - a big edge to second slip. Tikolo immediately makes a motion to say the ball bounced
a play and a miss there
on the money - well he is a trainee accountant - and only defence will do
on the spot and the batsman shoulders arms, allowing the ball to rush on to the keeper - well judged
defended to gully off the back foot
dabbed to point
walks into the shot, looking to on-drive, but doesn't quite time the ball
stabs the ball into the ground after failing to move his feet in a cut shot
walks forward to defend on the front foot, standing tall
short, wide and that keeps low, allowing Billcliff the chance to cut that forcefully to point; he misses out, though, crashing it down into the ground and straight to the fielder
plays that one off the toes behind square
on leg stump and there's an ambitious shout for Parker, who is unmoved other than to shake his head - that was easily going down the leg-side
oversteps with the effort
comes forward to defend, pushing that one into the covers
a touch too full and Billcliff times that exquisitely very straight, just to say on the on-side
on the money and that's defended forward
defended forward again
on the dot, and that's defended
more defence again
tidy bowling, giving nothing away
"wait" is the wise decision as the end of the Powerplays is brought up with a tickle to gully
on the dot
hit behind square
driven to mid-off
pushed to square but a misfield allows them to come through for a second
worked into the covers
on the button and that's beaten the man at short third man allowing them to come back for a second
the batsman can only defend here
defence
tidy stuff from Varaiya, another defensive
a bit of turn but well controlled
yet more defence
defence once more
defended again
defended forward
plenty of tweak as that nips in at the batsman who defends on the back foot
just loses his line, there, and that's worked in front of square for a quick single
defended on the front foot
defended again, great area
down on one knee, attempts a sweep, but that crashes off the pad instead
played forward
the tidy stuff continues, on the dot again
once more that's the spot, once more that's a dot
nibbles that one into the covers
moves on to his back foot to look to find room to work that to mid-on, doesn't find room, and the ball trickles there slowly
defended this time
neat footwork, striding forward and into that shot, a neat little flick off the front foot
goes on to his back foot to defend, but the ball doesn't get up as high as expected, and he ends up patting it back down
tickled into the leg-side this time
up there, another good ball, and yet  more defence results
and that's the 100 up, with a firm punch of a cover drive; good fielding on the boundary with a successful dive
comes forward and defends over that one

ah! That should have been out stumped by a mile... instead it was just by a whisker. The batsman raced right down the track and would have been well, well out if the stumping had been taken first time - but the bat's just in the air as he tries to slide it back. A deserved wicket for Varaiya, there
defending first up
more defence, just getting the measure of the pitch early on
cheeky sweep, cheeky strike-stealing
on a good length, slow and loopy and almost asking to be hit, but just too well placed to be struck away
defended again
defended this time
driven to long-on and is there a run on? "Oh yes, mate"
worked into midwicket and that's a quick single
straight back to the bowler, with a bump ball that's easily picked up
on leg, and that's swept down to one of two men out on the boundary
defended this time
sharp work from the bowler, diving to his right to stop the return hit
comes down the track to straight-drive forcefully through the off-side
tidy ball, well defended over
worked into the covers
drives that into his foot, ouch
steps back to try to work that through mid-on, but it's too much of a good length for the ideal shot, instead he manages a touch of nurdling
movement in the air and the bowler does well to dive over the ball, there
gets well over the ball to drive it off the toes in front of midwicket
a quick single into the leg-side, driven to mid-on
worked to square leg for a quick single
defended on the money
defending once more
even more defence
driven into the covers
a touch of extra loop nearly pays off - Billcliff going for the aerial drive but it lands in space inside the cover boundary
presses the bat to paddle-sweep that to fine leg
comes down the track to think about driving, doesn't

he's gone! Davison is gone! That's a huge wicket, bowled neck and crop and it's another deserved wicket for the spinners. Davison was completely deceived by that one which nipped right back in at him and took his stumps and Kamande's shimmy-shake of a celebration, while not quite Sreesanth-esque, is nevertheless a treat
full, but on leg, and the batsman gets on top of the spin to work it over in front of midwicket
on leg, and turned away again
on leg and that's worked to the man in close at short, wide fine leg
the bowler pushes him on to the back foot and he can only defend
worked to the man in front of midwicket. Billcliff scrunches up his nose at not being able to find the gap
short, wide and that's cut straight to the man at cover
hit into the midwicket region
goes to sweep it from the off-side, misses, and that crashes into his body
defended
risky sweep shot in front of the sticks, but that runs away
drops that short and it's pulled down to midwicket
comes forward to defend
tries to drive forward, but drives it into his toes
tickled fine off the pad
worked off the front foot to midwicket
defended
defended this time
tries to sweep that, misses, it crashes into his body and there's a big shout of "Owwwzzzzeeee?" 'E's safe
nudged to midwicket
"Catch it!" suggests Tikolo as that's ballooned up to the vacant long-on area
defended this time
tries to sweep, fails - more than a hint of frustration in that shot
played round the ball - it didn't turn that much, but it was flatter and quicker... and it sneaked through bat and pad
driven to cover
defended this time
Mulla has no answers to that one, either - it spun and bounced high at him and he could only defend
this one kept low, and he got over it to defend
swept low to fine leg
worked to midwicket and there's a quick single. Billcilff unimpressed with something, not sure what
pitches outside off, spins back in, and that's defended down
outside off, driven through cover and there's an optimistic shout of "Catch it!" as the fielder dives over the ball, once it had already bounced
driven off the toes with a flick to midwicket
worked forward to the cover
driven back to the bowler
dragged down and that's swept away
worked to square leg
driven to cover
pushed to cover
on the money and defended
a half-shout for lbw but it would have missed the sticks
a quick single driven forward
eased out to long-on
ooh, tries to cut that off the back foot, misses, and that narrowly fails to shave the under-edge
defended this time
"Catchaaaa..." The cry tails off as the ball bounces short of cover
worked into midwicket
easy single into the midwicket region
short and wide and that's cut off the back foot
pops into the vacant short leg area
rushed out to deep square leg, where the ball's quickly thrown back in
worked into the midwicket area
short ball and that's lifted into the square leg area
pushed out off the back foot, but doesn't make enough room to work it to mid-off
on the money and that's defended over
pushed up there and that's defended
worked into the covers
played out to point
worked off the back foot, again to point
horrible hoick - attempted aerial drive takes a very thick outside edge
down on one knee and pulls that square
a soft end for Billcliff, popping a nothing shot back to Tikolo who crashes down with agility to take a low two-handed catch
"How was that?" they wonder - it's most certainly not out, missing the stumps
driven to cover and some alert fielding, diving over, and on to, that one
driven to long-on
pitches outside off and it's played down off the back foot
a lone appeal from the keeper for a thin edge. The umpire's not-out decision was correct
driven forward
works back to try to make room, but can only drive without power, to the bowler
dabbed down to third man
wideish, but the umpire lets him off
spins in from outside off and that's just nudged gently into the covers
ooh, living dangerously there with that one which popped up to midwicket - an attempted doosra from Tikolo
worked to the midwicket region
rushed out off the front foot with a clip in front of midwicket
pitches straight and that's a tidy sweep square to bring up the 150
driven down into the ground off the back foot back to the bowler
nibbled into the covers and a direct hit would have removed Mulla - as it is there's an overthrow and they scramble two
rushed up there and raps the pads, but the Canadians squeeze out a run
short, straight and that one pops up off the bat into the covers
short, wide and what's this? Could it be a boundary? It is - a very well struck cut behind point off the back foot
using the pace again to run that one down to third man
straight drive this time
a huge heave and that's a really poor spill in the field by Ongondo, who was too casual in his approach. Mulla swung that high in the air and it was put down on the off side
defended forward this time
outside off and he fails to lay bat on it this time
driven to mid-on
driven to mid-off this time
down on one knee, tries to sweep, misses and the ball clatters into his body and plops, harmlessly, on to the ground
bangs that one in, it doesn't lift, and the batsman eases it down to third man
straight, full, and that's driven out to long-on
straight, and that's taken from middle with an attempted on-drive
full toss pulled away to deep square leg where it wasn't tidily dealt with by Shah, but he did well in the end to return
another full toss sliced down to third man for a single
six! And a big one! That's gone a long way, that pull shot off a full toss, right into the midwicket stand
short, dabbed to third man, and there's some excitement from the Kenya fielders, sensing a run out chance

Ongondo makes no mistake this time and it's smiles all round for the guys in green. Another huge swipe and Mulla doesn't muller that, sending it high and straight over to Ongondo at short third man who breaks into a broad beam as he holds on
outside off and that's driven without much power to cover
that turns away from the lefthander who leaves it
driven forward
shot! The ball pitches outside off and that's taken from there over in front of midwicket with a flat-bat smash. Nice!
short and that's worked easily enough down to third man
big heave at that one to one which pitches wide - completely misses
wide again and that's hit with some power - but not quite timed - to the sweeper on the off-side boundary

horrible flash - stepping back to that one for a waft. But, hello, some even more horrible cricket... The keeper lobbed it back to the bowler, but it went over his head, and the covering fielder returned to the keeper. Meanwhile, Bhatti had decided the run was on, but was left stranded when Dhaniram refused to set off. Oh dear
more trouble - driven off the back foot to cover and the non-striker is nearly run out without facing a ball, but there's a miss
moves on to his back foot and dabs that into the covers
on the button, and driven easily to cover
pitches straight, turns to leg and that's worked for an easy single into the leg-side
reverse sweep straight to third man, more confusion, and Cummins is going after that - he was well stranded at the non-striker's end
drops that one wide and the batsman has time to run that one down to third man
on the money and that's defended
ooh, a thick inside edge nearly dribbles back on to the stumps, but misses and it's collected by Ouma
oh, dabs at that one which flirts through to the keeper, popping just a touch on its way
nips back in off the seam, sits up a bit, and that's dabbed to third man
slower ball clubbed away on the on-side, and there's a casual one-handed pick-up inside the boundary
thin edge, full toss, and that boundary will be well received, even though it's not where he had meant to send it
picked up off the toes and that's flicked uppishly behind square
short, on leg, and that's worked out to cover - the run-out was a direct hit but he way out; just trying to get one final boost

inn2.comm: over the wicket, that pops up at the righthander, who pokes it down in defence
across the righthander, a touch of swing, but not near enough the batsman to be a threat
straight and true and the question's asked, but a sliver of inside edge saved the batsman, as he nudged that to the on-side
oh dear, a very wide
on off stump, fended down to the gully region, where it's picked up tidily
that's found the gap through cover, the batsman playing the swing well with a confident push to get off the mark
right up there and a hint of inswing and the batsman nearly trips over in his rush to bring the bat down on the ball in defence
drops that one down short - a loosener - and it's well put away in front of midwicket, pulling it from off stump
a better length immediately and that's defended down off the back foot
swings away down the off side - just a little too much for Umpire Parker's liking
on the money, defended forward, there's no run, but just to make sure there's a loud call of "No!"
good shape, a touch wide, swinging away and the batsman goes probing
on the money and that's defended forward on the front foot
defended on the back foot this time
pushed across the righthander, wideish, and that's chopped down to wide third man
on the money, and driven forward; a good piece of fielding - a slide at cover - but the batsmen would have been just to say home
worked off the hips down to the man at short fine leg
a hint of swing, negotiated by a drive to cover
great square cut and that rockets away
right up there and that's defended on the back foot to cover
pushed up there and that's defended down into the gully region
down the channel, lots of swing, but wide enough to be left alone
did what it said on the tin - went wide
jaffa, and that's not picked by the bat
excellent ball again, arcing tantalizingly past the outside edge - third time lucky?
good line and length this time, the batsman coming forward to defend
another defence to finish with
defended on the back foot with the full face of the bat
more defence
top shot! Waited for that one, it pitched up and there was a hint of swing into the pad but he got into a good position and slammed that in front of midwicket
huge six! Short and bashed over midwicket with a good, clean hit - he got right underneath that one and hit it high and long
tucked into the cover region
driven into the short midwicket area where it's easily picked up
defended on the back foot
more swing - the ball's been swinging all day - and the batsman flashes at it, but misses
straight and rears a tad, as well as moving off the seam - Obuya gets over it, though, to defend
pitched in off the seam
very wide
defended into the covers
gone! Cummins strikes and he's the man who has been threatening. Consistent seam bowling gets the reward, Obuya reaching for that one and snicks it through to the keeper
goes for a big boost - and gets away with it. Didn't get hold of that pull shot properly and sends it high but into space
fires that into the leg-side and the batsman glances it fine
that one cuts in at the righthander off the seam, there's a stifled appeal - a slight edge on that
turned that into midwicket
good line, and that crashes off the bat into the short midwicket area
edge but didn't carry to first slip - that rounds off a good over
swings away, too wide
strays leg-side and that's tucked off the pads
defended this time
tip-and-run stuff into the covers
a no-ball - and that would have been wide, too - oops
left alone outside off stick
oh, another peach of a jaffa, if I'm not mixing my fruit metaphors there - that pitches on off, nips off the seam and then swings away past the outside edge
well played, steered down to third man off one which is just short of a good length
wide down the leg side
pushed up there, driven straight, and that went out to long-off
strays down leg and that's very wide
driven slowly to cover
short, cuts in off the seam, and that's worked behind point
slower ball, on a good length, and that's defended forward
defended off the back foot
defended forward into the covers this time
lovely ball again - most of the fielders behind the stumps went up for that - but there was no edge; very close, nevertheless
defended into the covers again
another wide, chased round
driven off the back foot into the covers
up there, and once again that's defended - some tidy bowling here
pushed into the covers
driven in front of midwicket
wide and zigzaggy kind of swing - doesn't really matter, it's still wide
defended on the front foot this time
testy delivery, flighting down the channel and the batsman has a fish, but fortunately for him, not an edge
left alone outside off - ah, yet another wide, that's the 11th this innings
left alone outside off this time
picked off the legs through the leg-side
Another wide, the 11th, well outside off stump and no doubts over that one
down the leg side and turned round the corner
flicked off his hips into the leg side, an easy couple
close to another wide, outside off stump and Ouma shapes to cut but doesn't move his feet and misses it
offcutter zips back and strikes Ouma on the pads, a loud shout but slipping down the leg
another borderline decision for Parker ... it could have been a wide but he kept his hands by his side
speared down the leg side, half stopped by the keeper but another wide
loud shout, Ouma shuffles across the stumps and is hit in front. Slightly too straight and he got the benefit despite Hawkeye's verdict that it was hitting leg stump.
heaved from outside off stump into the leg side
pushed into the off side

a crucial breakthrough, the ball pitches on middle and swings into the right hander who is trapped half forward and that is about as out as you can get. Both batsmen tend to shuffle across their stumps and if they miss, the bowler hits
short and pulled from outside off stump over midwicket for a well-hit four
too wide and Ouma puts everything into that but doesn't time it and the ball bobbles into the covers
dire bowling at this stage, that one started wide and got wider outside the off stump. An easy one for the umpire
give me strength ... yet another wide and that one could have been called for two wides, so far outside off stump was it
no shot there as Tikolo finds his feet
left alone
lovely clip to the left of midwicket, sweetly timed and pulled up two yards in from the rope
fends that one forward
like a dog after a postman, he chases that one down leg
tickoloed into the off-side
tries to drive that straight and it's snapped up by the bowler
good loop, ducking in at the batsman there, who can only jam his bat down on it to defend
driven through cover, splitting the two fielders
right up there, and that's fended forward along the ground, back to the bowler
takes that from outside off and works it into midwicket
defended forward
thinks about working that into the midwicket region, but it's a tame swish
worked in front of square and that's a quick single
turned that one softly behind square
ooh, it's all going on here - that was flicked through to the keeper, it crashed onto his pads and back onto the stumps. There was a shout but the batsman was well in
solid defence this time
defended forward
a full toss, gift wrapped, and that's picked off his toes and worked through midwicket
down leg, chased, but that's called wide
straight bat defended forward
worked into midwicket
tickled off the legs into midwicket
drives that slowly to mid-off
wide, chased round, and connects with a fine wisp down through fine leg
on a good length and that's just worked into the cover region
worked round behind square
tucked into the leg side this time, just in front of square
worked into the off side
tries to work that to fine leg, doesn't quite get hold of it and it shoots to short leg
smashed through the off side this time
wide down the off side now
wide and that's driven through cover
down leg side, there's an attempted stumping but the umpires don't even call for their third man; Umpire Rauf signals wide instead
driven to cover
short, wide, and smacked off the back foot towards point
driven straight and could have been close had Billcliff's throw been faster and more accurate. It wasn't
cut in off the seam back at the righthander who stands tall, waits for the ball, and defends with soft hands
a quick single
turned into the leg side
rushes that into the short midwicket region
driven to cover
on the button immediately - that's pushed right up there and well defended
another quick single - Kenya pushing the singles around nicely now
defended forward
tickled round well
too short, a bit of width and that's smashed away - four all the way
driven straight back to the bowler, along the ground, without much power
